    "body": "not sure if it will work with snapshots. In golang when I make a subscription to events when there is a re-org the same event is sent with a flag - removed. I don't think the same will happen when using snapshots.\r\n\r\nfor example, chain is at 1000, mine a TX which emits an event A - trigger a reorg the same event A is sent with a flag A-removed, usually right after that if the same TX is included in the new block the same event might be repeated without the remove flag to mark it that regardless of the re-org it is still included in the new block. Ideally to make the tests extensive both cases should be doable - reorg where the TX is included in the new block and a re-org where the TX same TX is not included in the new block.",
