    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> Now in post-Merge world - is this still even a thing? (I mean reorgs)\r\n\r\nyes this is still very much needed, eth switching to POS doesn't change the finality of a block, and when using other networks such as Polygon that have frequent deep reorgs, it still is a highly desired feature.\r\n\r\nlooking quick over the ethereumjs vm snapshot, revert and remine with the option of including or removing a transaction and being able to assert the correct events and state changes are made, or application logic handles reorg correctly would be a big win for most developers who have had to debug systems that do not have any reorg handling logic\r\n\r\n",
